ships/2849.html |title=Sunoil |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=4 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-167|1942|2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type IX submarine|Type IXC/40 submarine]] was depth charged and damaged in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] off the [[Canary Islands]], Spain (approximately {{coord|27|47|N|15|00|W}}) by a [[Lockheed Hudson]] aircraft of [[No. 233 Squadron RAF|233 Squadron]], [[Royal Air Force]]. She was scuttled the next day. All 52 crew survived.<ref name=U167>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u167.htm |title=U-167 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=6 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-635||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean south east of Iceland ({{coord|58|20|N|31|52|W}}) by a [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]] aircraft of [[No. 120 Squadron RAF|120 Squadron]], Royal Air Force with the loss of all 47 crew.<ref name=U635>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u635.htm |title=U-635 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Vaalaren||2}}\n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy HX 231]]: The cargo ship romped ahead of the convoy. She was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean (approximately {{coord|58|N|34|W}}) by {{GS|U-229||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of all 38 crew.<ref name=Vaalaren>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/2845.html |title=Vaalaren |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=10 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Waroonga||2}}\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy HX 231]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and damaged in the Atlantic Ocean by {{GS|U-635||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). She was then torpedoed and damaged further by {{GS|U-630||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 19 of the 132 people aboard. S