.Y. |year=1965 |page=403 |isbn=<!--none-->}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kosei Maru|1920|2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and heavily damaged in the Pacific Ocean ({{coord|08|45|N|147|10|E}}) by {{USS|Tunny|SS-282|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). Four crewmen were killed. She sank under tow two days later.<ref name=seekrieg194304/><ref name=StanL>{{cite web |url= http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/WWIStandardShipsL-W.htm#L-M-N |title=WWI Standard Built Ships L \u2013 W |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=8 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Kosei8282_t.htm |title=Kosei Maru |publisher=www.combinedfleet.com |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMNZS|Moa|T233|6}}\n|flag={{navy|New Zealand|1941}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|Bird|minesweeper}} was bombed and sunk in Tulagi Harbour by Japanese aircraft with the loss of five of her 35 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-644||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC submarine]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Norwegian Sea]] west of [[Narvik]], Norway ({{coord|69|38|N|5|40|W}}) by {{HMS|Tuna|N94|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) with the loss of all 45 crew.<ref name=U644>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u644.htm |title=U-644 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==8 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=8 April 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Castillo Montealegre||2}}\n|flag={{flag|Spain|1938}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] off [[French Sudan]] ({{coord|9|46|N|16|50|W}}) by {{GS|U-123|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 12 of her 43 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Inkpen|T225|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=CM>{{cite web|url= http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?31776 |title=MV Castillo Montealegre (+1943) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=12 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=Times200443>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Spanish Ship Sunk |day_of_week=Tuesday |date=20 April 1943 |page_number=4 |issue=49525 |column=B}}</ref><ref name=CMU123>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/2854.html |title=Castillo Montealegre |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=24 February 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"APR\">[http://www.perezreverte.com/articulo/patentes-corso/744/el-misterio-del-castillo-montealegre/ El misterio del 'Castillo Montealegre'], 4 March 2013, [[XLSemanal]], [[Arturo P\u00e9rez-Reverte]]. A syndicated column from the point of view of a nephew of a friend of a survivor.</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Foggia||2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off the coast of [[French Tunisia|Tunisia]] by {{HMS|Unshaken|P54|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194304/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet patrol boat|No. 045||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[MO-class small guard ship#MO-4 type|''MO-4''-class]] [[patrol vessel]]  was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_mo4.htm |title=MO-class small guard ship, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet patrol boat|No. 054||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[MO-class small guard ship#MO-4 type|''MO-4''-class]] [[patrol vessel]]  was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_mo4.htm |title=MO-class small guard ship, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Toyo Maru|Harima, 1937|2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk off [[Rabaul]], [[New Guinea]] by [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]] a