K}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[landing craft support (mortar)]] was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.navypedia.org/ships/uk/brit_aws_lcalcsm.htm |title=LCA Assault Landing Craft and LCS(M) Support Landing Craft, Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=4 April 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Leesee||2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[White Sea]] off the [[Makkaur Lighthouse]], Norway by Soviet aircraft. There were 11 dead and 40 survivors.<ref name=seekrieg194304/><ref name=Huan/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=55255&sid=b64d81afc6dc3bf6ebf262ded5ddeaf9 |title=Soviet torpedo bomber victories during WWII |publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=28 March 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M-471||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]] was bombed and sunk in the [[North Sea]] off [[Den Helder]], the Netherlands.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=6116062|shipname=M-471 |accessdate=16 October 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet patrol boat|No. 0212||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[MO-class small guard ship#MO-4 type|''MO-4''-class]] [[patrol vessel]]  was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_mo4.htm |title=MO-class small guard ship, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Rosenborg||2}}\n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy RU 71]]: The cargo ship straggled behind the convoy. She was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] (approximately {{coord|61|N|15|W}}) by {{GS|U-385||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 28 of her 30 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{SS|Goodwin||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}).<ref name=Rosenborg>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/2882.html |title=Rosenborg |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=19 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Rouennais||2}}\n|flag={{flag|France}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the Atlantic Ocean off [[Casablanca]], [[Spanish Protectorate of Morocco|Morocco]] ({{coord|34|04|N|7|23|W}}) with the loss of sixteen of her 55 crew.<ref name=Rouennais>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/2884.html |title=Rouennais |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=26 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-203||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean off [[Cape Farewell, Greenland]] ({{coord|55|05|N|42|25|W}}) by [[Fairey Swordfish]] aircraft of [[811 Naval Air Squadron|811 Squadron]], [[Fleet Air Arm]], based on {{HMS|Biter|D97|6}} and by {{HMS|Opportune|G80|6}} and {{HMS|Pathfinder|G10|6}} (all {{navy|UK}}) with the loss of ten of her 48 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minelayer|Wullenwever||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minelayer]] struck mines and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1143 |title=German minelayers Requisitioned French |publisher=Warshipsww2.Eu |accessdate=21 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204173330/http://www.warshipsww2.eu/lode.php?language=E&period=&idtrida=1143 |archive-date=4 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|YP-481}}\n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The [[yard patrol boat]] grounded and was wrecked in the Atlantic Ocean off [[Charleston, South Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Patrol and training craft YP |url=http://shipbuildinghistory.com/history/smallships/yp.htm |accessdate=31 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.arc